44_001_011.Text: They said, “Galilee residents! Why are you standing here looking towards the sky? Yes, this is that very Jesus, who has been lifted up to heaven from among you. But take courage! Just as you have seen him going up, like that only one day he will come again from heaven.

44_001_012.Text: Then the apostles came back from that hill to Jerusalem. This hill is about one kilometer distance from there. *

44_001_012.Text: 1:12 “Is one kilometer distance" in the Greek, “Is on the distance of a day of rest": According to the Jewish custom, they were not allowed to do any work on the day of rest. For example, (they) had permission to move a distance of one kilimeter, which they called, “The distance of the day of rest.”

44_001_013.Text: Reaching there, they went to the upper room where they were staying. These were their names: Peter, John, James, Andrew, Philip, Thomas, Bartholomew, Matthew and Alphaeus’ son, James, Simon the Zealot and James’s son, Judas.

44_001_014.Text: All these disciples kept praying together, having become one-minded. And the mother of Jesus, Mary, and his brothers and several other women also used to participate with them.

44_001_015.Text: In those days, when about 120 believers had gathered together, then Peter, having stood up among them, said,

44_001_016.Text: “My believer brothers and sisters! Although Jesus had chosen Judas as a special disciple for serving along with us, even so, in the end, he brought the ones coming to catch Jesus to Jesus.

44_001_016.Text: “But, taking this thing, don’t take worry/trouble, because whatever he did that was to fulfill the thing written in our holy religious scriptures, which the Holy Spirit had prophesied many years ago by King David.”

44_001_018.Text: (From the earnings of unrighteousness, which Judas had received as a reward for having Jesus caught, a field was bought. Then in that very field he fell in such a way that, in falling down, his stomach split open and his intestines fell out.
